  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Architectural Associate",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>· Knowledge of fundamental principles and practices of architecture, construction materials and methods, and building codes;</p>\n<p>· Research on materials, methods, and construction techniques;</p>\n<p>· Interpret design concept and translating them into workable solution and ensure design quality and authority compliance;</p>\n<p>· Conceptualize and present design proposal;</p>\n<p>· Assist and support Architect in executing multiple architectural projects;</p>\n<p>· Assist in tender drawings and material specifications;</p>\n<p>· Assist in liaising and coordinating with consultants and contractors;</p>\n<p>· Assist project Architect on site implementation.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>· Recognized Degree in Architecture or equivalent, registrable with Board of Architects, Singapore;</p>\n<p>· Well-verse in Singapore BCA BIM e-submission process, requirements and guidelines;</p>\n<p>· Excellent knowledge and experience of Autodesk Building Design Suite software including Revit Architecture;</p>\n<p>· Completed BCA Academy’s BIM Modeling and BIM Management would be an added advantage;</p>\n<p>· Fresh graduates are welcome to apply.</p>",
